RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE OCTOBER 2, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED HOT CAT Stalked four wide from the outset, travelled well within himself into the bend three wide, loomed large at the eighth pole, surged through stretch, got up in final strides. BLUE CHIP BETTY Hustled from the blocks but was outsprinted by LIL MISS MISCHIEF to the lead, settled on the rail into the turn, rallied along the rail through the lane, made the lead around the sixteenth pole but was caught in the late stages. LIL' MISS MISCHIEF Broke on top and made the lead easily, led clearly to just inside the eighth pole while also shifting to the two path, outfinished down the stretch. CURRENTLY KRAZY Moved well off the pace while widest of all, circled in the four path on the turn, came with a willingly and belated run through the stretch. LOST THE MINISTER Was outrun by all early and could only progress beyond tiring foes. CANT DO THE DANSE Missed the break a touch, moved up quickly to stalk three wide, never improved. MIDNIGHT DRAMA Stalked along the rail from the break, idled when called upon in the same path at the quarter pole and never progressed. SWITCH BACK Stalked two wide in a throng of horses, got in tight into the turn and checked out of a spot at the quarter pole, recovered by swinging to the eight path for the stretch run, finished evenly.

ENTRY.NAME: Lost the Minister
ENTRY.OWNER: Crotts James E and Jaime Jr Jacobo
ENTRY.COMMENT: Outrun by all early, only passed tiring

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Drama
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalked rail, idled rail 1/4, no progression

ENTRY.NAME: Switch Back
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk 2w, in tight turn, checked 1/4, swung 8p, evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Cant Do the Danse
ENTRY.OWNER: Pallanes, Alan J. and Arnold, Pete
ENTRY.COMMENT: Touch slow break, stalk 3w, never improved

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Chip Betty
ENTRY.COMMENT: Outsprinted to lead, rail, vied lane, led 1/16, caught

ENTRY.NAME: Lil' Miss Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke on top, led, 2p str, outfinished stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Red Hot Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk 4w, 3w turn, loom 1/8, surged, in time

ENTRY.NAME: Currently Krazy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Well off pace widest, circle 4p turn, willing belated run

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIND BUT SHE LIES Enforced position two wide into the first turn, cleared to rail into the backside, led through the backstretch and around the turn, maintained advantage into the stretch while shifting to the two path, re-engaged at the sixteenth, held on. LOVELY LOLA Pinched slightly at the start, forced to settle in the rear, swung three wide in the move to the backstretch, commenced three wide at the five-sixteenths pole with steady progress, dove to the rail at the three-sixteenths, surged inside of rival, repelled late. LITTLEQUEENOFMEAN Moved three wide into the first turn, pressed two wide into the backstretch, in the three path into the lane, evenly home. YOU NEVER CALL Traveled four wide into the first turn, settled three wide while stalking the top duo, remained in touch to the eighth pole while forced to the four path, faded late. ARCTIC FIRE Hustled from the inside draw to hold the rail but was ultimately cleared and forced to stalk in behind the top trio, stayed in touch to the three eighths before dropping back, drifted to the four path around the turn, had nothing left late. TOSSAPENNYDOWN Settled in the rear between, maintained position until being called upon at the three-sixteenths in the three path, never menaced. AWESOME GALAXY Traveled off the pace on the rail and never improved position.

ENTRY.NAME: Arctic Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled, force stalk ins, drop back 3/8, drift 4p, nothing late

ENTRY.NAME: Lovely Lola
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pinch start, 3w in rear, move 3w 5/16, rail 3/16, surge, repelled

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Galaxy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Off pace rail, never improved

ENTRY.NAME: Tossapennydown
ENTRY.COMMENT: In rear between, called upon 3/16 3p, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Kind But She Lies
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w 1st, rail back, led, advantage 2p str, reengage 1/16, held

ENTRY.NAME: Littlequeenofmean
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, 2w press, 3p 1/8, evenly late

ENTRY.NAME: You Never Call
ENTRY.OWNER: Kern Jan and Larson Wayne M
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w first, 3w stalk, in touch to 1/8 4p, faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 9300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 2, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIGER BY HIS TAIL Tucked in behind the early leaders on the first turn, stayed in the fray until advancing between at the five-sixteenths, swung to the three path into the lane, tussled with GOLD STAR STUDENT through the stretch, kept finding to score. GOLD STAR STUDENT Immediately broke to the lead, opened up around the first turn, maintained a healthy advantage to the stretch, drifted to the two path into the lane, fought inside rival, outfinished. SAN GIORGIO Mildly hopped at the start, settled off the pace on the rail, sifted inside of horses on the turn, rallied willingly along the rail for show honors. JUSTIN'S LADY Moved three wide into the first turn, tracked along in the four path, made a three wide bid at the quarter pole, finished evenly. FIGHT ME Stumbled to nose at the break, lagged far behind until entering the far turn, swung widest in the seven path, came with a belated late run. ECHO ALPHA SIX Traveled widest while off the path in the six path into the first turn, stayed widest up the backstretch, made a four wide move on the far turn, came into the stretch in the six path, flattened out late. HUGHIE'S HOLIDAY Forced four wide into the first turn, tracked between horses up the backstretch, lost ground on the turn, emptied down the stretch. BUMPY CUP Chased two wide into the first turn, stalked in the same lane up the backstretch, backed out at the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Gold Star Student
ENTRY.COMMENT: Immediately to lead, opened up, maintained, drift 2p, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Bumpy Cup
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w 1st, stalk 2w, backed out 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: San Giorgio
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hop start, off pace rail, sift ins turn, rail rally, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Fight Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stumble break, lagged, swung 7p, belatedly

ENTRY.NAME: Tiger by His Tail
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tuck in rail, adv 5/16, swung 3p lane, tussle str, kept finding

ENTRY.NAME: Justin's Lady
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w 1st, tracked 4p, 3w bid 1/4, evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Hughie's Holiday
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st, tracked between, lost ground turn, empty stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Echo Alpha Six
ENTRY.COMMENT: Widest off pace 6p, 4w turn, 6p lane, flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER THAT HAVE STARTED AT THE 2023 RILLITO PARK MEET AND HAVE NOT FINISHED BETTER THAN THIRD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR. TROUTMAN Hard sent to the lead from the outside draw, moved three wide into the first turn, went one path inward to duel on the outside, stayed in toe with rival all the way to the end of the stretch, lifted in final strides to get up in time. SHARK HARBOR Hustled from inner draw, held the rail throughout, dueled inside through the backstretch, kept in fight to the line but could not muster enough. TIZ TENACIOUS Stalked two wide throughout, loomed in the three path on the turn, tried through the lane, third best. EMPEROR'S CHOICE Brushed slightly outside at the start, between top flight runners into the first turn, took hold to stalk right in behind on the inside paths, idled when running picked up on the turn, came home evenly and on the wrong lead down the stretch. ORATORY GLORY Settled on the rail into the first turn, tracked inside of rivals, swung to the four path for the stretch, finished with mild interest. OUTLAW BY NATURE Forced into the four path on the first turn, dove to the rail up the backstretch and held path throughout, came under a ride at the three-eighths, progressed on the turn, finished evenly. BULLY RIDE Moved in the three path in the second flight, moved out a path for the stretch, was no menace. TRACK BOUND Tracked off the pace two deep throughout, dropped back at the quarter pole, not asked home.

ENTRY.NAME: Shark Harbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: Dueled inside from the outset to wire, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Emperor's Choice
ENTRY.COMMENT: Brush start, btwn 1st, stalk ins, idled turn, wrong lead, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Oratory Glory
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail 1st, tracked inside, swung 4p lane, mild lane

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Tenacious
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk 2w, loom 3p turn, tried lane, third best

ENTRY.NAME: Track Bound
ENTRY.COMMENT: Track 2 deep, dropped back 1/4, not asked

ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st, to rail 2nd, under ride 3/8, progress turn, evenly

ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st, 4p lane, no menace

ENTRY.OWNER: Ayon Moreno Miguel and Tijuana Racing Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hard sent, 3w 1st, duel outs to line, up in time

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINISTERSDON'TLIE Tucked in a pocket when cleared off by ROYAL TAP, bided time while confidently handled in behind dueling leaders, waited till seam opened along the rail at the eighth pole, took off down the lane and ridden out. ROYAL TAP Dueled outside of rival from the break, stayed in battle through the turn, shifted to the three path into the lane, no match for eventual winner, just bested the rest. NORTH DAWN Cleared to lead, joined in duel by an outside rival, stayed in fray to the eighth when shifting out a path, vied for minors down the lane. ALEX'S GIRL Bobbled at the break, sat off the dueling leaders, circled boldly three wide, wrong lead stretch, flattened late. WICKED BLUE Broke slightly outwards, lagged far behind, commenced at the quarter pole, three wide lane, mildly late. HULA KING Settled on the rail in the second flight, between rivals turn, outrun late. ROCKY JACK Moved four wide into the first turn, shifted to the rail on the turn, failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Budweiser Pima County Classic S. RILLITO RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 90. Stakes Purse 24000. FOR HORSES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. No trials and no nomination. An entry fee of $250 to be paid at the time of entry. Horses that have started at the 2023 Rillito meet are preferred. Second preference is earnings in 2022 and 2023. Maidens are least pre ferred. Same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time of entry. Weights: 3 years old . 124, Older . 126.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEEDING STYLE Stalked in the two path from the break, maintained position until moving to the lead at the five-sixteenths, opened up on the field at the three-sixteenths, drew off to a convincing win. TWO GUNS Stalked three wide, swung four wide third turn, flew late, second best. BIG CITY BANE Tracked two wide between rivals opening stages, idled on the far turn, shifted to the six path for the stretch run, finished up with a belated run. TEXAS LONG BOW Stalked four wide and widest early, moved two wide first time by the stands, forced three wide on the last turn, finished up evenly. TAKE CHARGE DEPUTY Tracked in the third flight along the rail, maintained inner paths throughout, ridden at the three-eighths pole but failed to improve. HPNOTIQ RHYTHM Led from the outset, maintained until being overtaken by the quarter pole, empty late. PEACE OF EKATI Detached in the early stages, switched out and ridden at the three-eighths pole, fanned to the four path on the last turn, flattened out down the stretch. POLITICAL RIOT Tracked the widest of all throughout in about the five path, asked to pick up at the seven-sixteenths, never a menace.
